Optional class offers a wide range of method to interact with it like `orElse()`, `ifPresent()`, `orElse()`, etc. Avoid blindly using `get()`, unless you didn&#39;t check that value is present, which is in many cases isn&#39;t the most convenient way to deal with it. Like in the code below, `ifPresent()` is being used to proceed with the logic if value is present.

